    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "31 - TRIBOROUGH BRIDGE, NEW YORK CITY",
      "TRIBOROUGH BRIDGE:\nShowing main span\nover the East River,\nwhich is 1,380 feet long be-\nween towers and the two side spans are 705 feet\nlong. It is 17½ miles long. Connects three New\nYork City\nboroughs, Manhattan,\nBronx,\nand\nQueens. Work was begun in 1929 and completed\nin 1936.\n13.\nHope you like thes\nver- a nue decorat\nкане\n\" Нели\npress\ni Ул\nSlo .\nMANHATTAN POST CARD PUBLISHING CO., INC., N. Y. c.\nPOST CARD\nTHIS SIDE IS FOR THE ADDRESS\nPLACE\nONE CENT\nSTAMP\nHERE\nMADE IN U. S. A."
    ],
